In [301]:

In [302]:
pubs_dept_OA_sum = pubs_dept_OA_sum.reset_index().copy()

pubs_dept_OA_sum.rename(columns={'OA_bool':'OA_true'}, inplace=True)
pubs_dept_OA_count.rename(columns={'OA_bool':'total_pubs'}, inplace=True)

Now for individual years, and merge them back into overall one:

In [303]:
for year in years:
    yearPubs = pubs.loc[pubs['PubDate'].str.contains(str(year))]
    pubs_dept_OA_sum = yearPubs.groupby('Primary group')['OA_bool'].sum().copy()
    pubs_dept_OA_count = yearPubs.groupby('Primary group')['OA_bool'].count().copy()
    pubs_dept_OA_sum = pubs_dept_OA_sum.reset_index().copy()
    pubs_dept_OA_count = pubs_dept_OA_count.reset_index().copy()
    pubs_dept_OA_sum.rename(columns={'OA_bool':'OA_true'+str(year)}, inplace=True)
    pubs_dept_OA_count.rename(columns={'OA_bool':'pubs'+str(year)}, inplace=True)
    pubs_dept_OA = pubs_dept_OA_sum.merge(pubs_dept_OA_count, on = 'Primary group')
    pubs_dept_OA['Perc_OA'+str(year)] = (pubs_dept_OA['OA_true'+str(year)] / pubs_dept_OA['pubs'+str(year)]) * 100
    pubs_dept_OA.to_csv('pubs_dept_OA_'+str(year)+'.csv')
    pubs_dept_OA_all = pubs_dept_OA_all.merge(pubs_dept_OA, on = 'Primary group')

In [312]:
with open('OA_Publisher_Totals.csv', 'w', newline='', encoding='utf-8') as f:
    writer = csv.writer(f)
    writer.writerow(['College', 'Publisher', 'Total_Publications', 'OA_Publications', 'Perc_OA'])
    for coll in colleges:
        collDF = pubs4.loc[(pubs4['college'] == coll)]
        coll_publishers = collDF['Publisher_rev'].unique() 
        for publisher in coll_publishers:
            pubPubs = collDF.loc[(collDF['Publisher_rev'] == publisher)]
            pubSum = len(pubPubs)
            OAsum = pubPubs['OA_bool'].sum()
            if OAsum == 0:
                OAperc = 0
            else:
                OAperc = (OAsum/pubSum)*100
            writer.writerow([coll, publisher, pubSum, OAsum, round(OAperc,2)])
